<paragraph blockId="98.[189,1398,1964,2027]" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Troschel" authorityYear="1842" box="[319,472,1964,1990]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Ophiacantha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="98" pageNumber="99" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[319,472,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="98" pageNumber="99">Ophiacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with moderately large LAPs displaying a rather knobby general aspect; single poorly defined, protruding spur on outer proximal edge; outer surface devoid of vertical striation, with
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="99.[189,1398,267,330]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">coarsely meshed stereom displaying thickened trabecular intersections; up to six large spine articulations proximally bordered by knobby, undulose ridge; tentacle notch invisible in external view.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
